  "original_title": "\u0db1\u0dd3\u0dad\u0dd2\u0da5\u0dba\u0ddd 350\u0d9a\u0dca \u0d85\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dbd\u0d9a\u0dbb\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0db1\u0dca \u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd4\u0dc0\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db4\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dd3 \u0dc3\u0dd2\u0da7\u0dd2\u0dad\u0dd2",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "350 lawyers represent the strugglers",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Colombo Fort Acting Magistrate Mr. Jayantha Dias Nanayakkara today (22) released the nine suspects, including lawyer Nuwan Bopage, who were arrested in the early morning incident at the Galumuwadora protest site on a cash bail of 10,000 rupees each and 2 body bails of 5 lakh rupees. ) ordered.",
        "The court called the case related to this incident and ordered the bail of the suspects to be deposited in the court on the next day, and also ordered them to be released on personal bail.",
        "Among these nine suspects, two suspects are being treated in hospital and both of them were granted bail by the court.",
        "On behalf of the suspects, a panel of over three hundred and fifty lawyers led by President's Lawyers Saliya Peiris, Sarath Jayamanna, Rienzi Arsakularatne and Upul Jayasuriya appeared before the court and presented the facts.",
        "Deputy Solicitor General Mr. Janaka Bandara representing the Attorney General, Colombo Central Division Senior Superintendent of Police Roshanda Dias, Assistant Superintendent of Police Villakawaarachichi and Fort Police Station Commander Sagara Liyanage appeared before the court."
      ],
